1
00:00:33,850 --> 00:00:39,750
Do you, Kazuomi, take Sayaka
as your lawfully wedded wife?

2
00:00:39,750 --> 00:00:41,810
<i>"The picture perfect husband and wife".</i>

3
00:00:41,810 --> 00:00:43,210
<i>Not many guests, huh?</i>

4
00:00:43,210 --> 00:00:44,580
<i>You think?</i>

5
00:00:44,580 --> 00:00:48,530
<i>He's got looks, and a solid career.
He's wasted on her.</i>

6
00:00:48,530 --> 00:00:50,070
<i>I can't stand them.</i>

7
00:00:50,070 --> 00:00:51,220
<i>Lame.</i>

8
00:00:51,220 --> 00:00:54,130
<i>She's practically begging for him.</i>

9
00:00:54,130 --> 00:00:55,790
<i>Does she feel no shame?</i>

10
00:00:55,790 --> 00:00:56,870
I do.

11
00:00:56,870 --> 00:00:58,580
I do.

12
00:01:08,910 --> 00:01:10,610
<i>What a bore.</i>

13
00:01:10,610 --> 00:01:13,430
<i>It's all practically routine at this point.</i>

14
00:01:13,430 --> 00:01:16,930
<i>I've seen my fair share of weddings.</i>

15
00:01:16,930 --> 00:01:20,400
<i>No one's ever objected at the altar,</i>

16
00:01:20,400 --> 00:01:22,990
<i>nor suddenly professed their love</i>

17
00:01:22,990 --> 00:01:27,760
<i>as a secret second suitor.</i>

18
00:01:34,820 --> 00:01:38,100
<i>Won't something interesting happen for once?</i>

19
00:01:38,100 --> 00:01:40,970
- Congrats!
- Congratulations!

20
00:01:51,160 --> 00:01:53,170
Sakuraba.

21
00:01:53,170 --> 00:01:54,200
Hello there.

22
00:01:54,200 --> 00:01:58,410
I underestimated how nerve-racking
a wedding would be.

23
00:01:59,990 --> 00:02:02,660
Your exhibition the other day was stunning.

24
00:02:02,660 --> 00:02:04,930
Sayaka shared the same sentiments.

25
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:10,000
See this? We visited after receiving
our first-look photos.

26
00:02:10,000 --> 00:02:11,410
I see.

27
00:02:11,410 --> 00:02:14,170
Yes. We're excited to see your shots
from the ceremony as well.

28
00:02:14,170 --> 00:02:15,550
Thank you.

29
00:02:15,550 --> 00:02:18,170
I'll talk to you again later.

30
00:02:26,980 --> 00:02:28,360
Looking good.

31
00:02:28,360 --> 00:02:30,620
Let me get another shot.

32
00:02:31,910 --> 00:02:33,850
Thank you.

33
00:02:41,770 --> 00:02:43,800
This tastes great.

34
00:02:43,800 --> 00:02:45,590
Blue champagne is a first, though.

35
00:02:45,590 --> 00:02:48,860
It's a memorable drink to both Sayaka and I.

36
00:02:48,860 --> 00:02:52,450
Hey, no getting wasted before the groom.

37
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:57,240
Are you alright?

38
00:02:59,390 --> 00:03:05,170
Yes, sorry.
I haven't performed for a crowd in ages.

39
00:03:06,400 --> 00:03:10,100
When did you begin learning violin?

40
00:03:10,100 --> 00:03:11,880
When I was three years old.

41
00:03:11,880 --> 00:03:15,780
Wow, that's quite young.

42
00:03:15,780 --> 00:03:19,070
My mother insisted.

43
00:03:19,070 --> 00:03:23,680
Then she must be excited
to hear you perform today.

44
00:03:29,150 --> 00:03:32,160
I held my wedding at this venue as well.

45
00:03:34,110 --> 00:03:36,770
You seem happy.

46
00:03:37,840 --> 00:03:39,910
Don't worry, Mrs. Sayaka.

47
00:03:39,910 --> 00:03:44,970
Happiness will find its way to you, too.

48
00:03:49,320 --> 00:03:51,090
You've got something on your cheek.

49
00:03:51,090 --> 00:03:52,730
- Seriously?
- Yeah.

50
00:03:52,730 --> 00:03:54,380
Right there.

51
00:03:54,380 --> 00:03:56,590
Well, look at that.

52
00:03:56,590 --> 00:03:58,030
Jeez...

53
00:03:59,880 --> 00:04:03,300
This has been a wonderful ceremony, ma'am.

54
00:04:03,300 --> 00:04:08,500
Thank you. We appreciate you all
for coming to join us today.

55
00:04:08,500 --> 00:04:12,510
Of course we'd come! We're Sayaka's besties.

56
00:04:12,510 --> 00:04:13,790
Anything for her big day.

57
00:04:13,790 --> 00:04:17,010
Yes, we're here for Sayaka.

58
00:04:18,220 --> 00:04:24,300
Sayaka and I have both been blessed
with such wonderful friends.

59
00:04:24,300 --> 00:04:25,850
You're embarrassing us.

60
00:04:29,770 --> 00:04:32,900
Guests, thank you for your patience.

61
00:04:32,900 --> 00:04:36,550
Mrs. Sayaka will now be performing
the violin for you all.

62
00:04:36,550 --> 00:04:39,870
Please enjoy her performance.

63
00:04:46,000 --> 00:04:47,290
Go, Sayaka!

64
00:04:47,290 --> 00:04:48,260
You got this!

65
00:04:48,260 --> 00:04:49,880
Give it your all.

66
00:06:13,830 --> 00:06:15,500
Sayaka!

67
00:06:17,250 --> 00:06:19,470
Sayaka!

68
00:06:23,080 --> 00:06:25,640
- Is she drunk?
- That can't be it.

69
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,090
- Sayaka!
- Sayaka!

70
00:06:27,090 --> 00:06:28,940
- Why?
- Someone call an ambulance!

71
00:06:28,940 --> 00:06:30,720
- Wake up, please!
- Sayaka! Sayaka!

72
00:06:30,720 --> 00:06:33,200
<i>What in the world is going on?</i>

73
00:06:33,200 --> 00:06:37,920
- <i>Am I dreaming?</i>
- We need an ambulance. It's an emergency.

74
00:06:37,920 --> 00:06:40,860
<i>I'm treading into the unknown.</i>

75
00:06:40,860 --> 00:06:43,820
<i>This hell unfolding before me</i>

76
00:06:43,820 --> 00:06:48,020
- <i>is far from the routine I'm used to.</i>
- Sayaka...

77
00:06:56,300 --> 00:06:57,610
Sayaka.

78
00:06:57,610 --> 00:06:59,850
Sayaka!

79
00:07:17,000 --> 00:07:18,410
Come here.

80
00:07:37,280 --> 00:07:41,420
<i>The bride collapsed while spitting up blood.</i>

81
00:07:41,420 --> 00:07:48,750
<i>What if someone had an ulterior motive
at that wedding?</i>

82
00:07:52,370 --> 00:07:56,140
How could this have happened?

83
00:07:56,140 --> 00:08:00,250
And during the wedding, no less...

84
00:08:01,710 --> 00:08:03,990
How absolutely embarrassing.

85
00:08:03,990 --> 00:08:05,350
What?

86
00:08:07,570 --> 00:08:10,090
Goodness...

87
00:08:10,090 --> 00:08:12,420
[Unhappiest wishes to you, Red Riding Hood]

88
00:08:22,280 --> 00:08:23,760
Mother.

89
00:08:25,620 --> 00:08:30,960
Sayaka never had any health issues, correct?

90
00:08:32,060 --> 00:08:36,010
Then we ought to report this after all.

91
00:08:36,010 --> 00:08:37,910
Absolutely not.

92
00:08:39,220 --> 00:08:42,000
Not the police.

93
00:08:42,000 --> 00:08:43,650
But Mother...

94
00:08:45,230 --> 00:08:47,690
Think this through, dear.

95
00:08:47,690 --> 00:08:52,110
The wedding was already chaotic,

96
00:08:52,110 --> 00:08:55,250
and now you wish to get the police involved?

97
00:08:55,250 --> 00:08:59,020
These sorts of rumors spread quick.

98
00:08:59,020 --> 00:09:01,220
But for Sayaka to remain at ease...

99
00:09:01,220 --> 00:09:03,980
Listen to me, Kazuomi.

100
00:09:03,980 --> 00:09:12,230
I truly appreciate you getting defensive
on my daughter's behalf.

101
00:09:12,230 --> 00:09:18,010
But please, calm yourself for a moment.

102
00:09:18,690 --> 00:09:23,630
Sayaka won't feel any better
knowing you blew this out of proportion.

103
00:09:23,630 --> 00:09:25,410
Isn't that right?

104
00:09:55,650 --> 00:09:57,070
Sakuraba?

105
00:09:57,070 --> 00:09:58,940
I apologize for visiting unannounced.

106
00:09:58,940 --> 00:10:02,160
Wait, how did you get my address?

107
00:10:02,160 --> 00:10:04,180
"How"?

108
00:10:05,180 --> 00:10:08,020
<i>Think back to when you visited my exhibition.</i>

109
00:10:08,020 --> 00:10:08,990
Thank you.

110
00:10:08,990 --> 00:10:10,710
[Name - Address - Phone number]

111
00:10:11,850 --> 00:10:13,480
Right, I forgot.

112
00:10:13,480 --> 00:10:16,220
Who is that at the door?

113
00:10:16,220 --> 00:10:18,320
Oh, this is...

114
00:10:18,320 --> 00:10:20,210
The name's Sakuraba, ma'am.

115
00:10:20,210 --> 00:10:24,960
I was the wedding photographer.

116
00:10:24,960 --> 00:10:27,890
I apologize for the trouble
our ceremony caused.

117
00:10:27,890 --> 00:10:32,800
Actually, I have some shots from yesterday.

118
00:10:36,630 --> 00:10:38,450
Would you like to take a look?

119
00:10:42,570 --> 00:10:45,360
My, these all look wonderful.

120
00:10:49,420 --> 00:10:52,990
This was to be their moment, and yet...

121
00:11:00,290 --> 00:11:03,480
I think I'll get going.

122
00:11:08,210 --> 00:11:12,610
Kazuomi. Keep in mind what I told you.

123
00:11:12,610 --> 00:11:16,460
Right, of course. I won't say a thing.

124
00:11:16,460 --> 00:11:20,030
Remember, this is for Sayaka.

125
00:11:34,310 --> 00:11:36,000
Here you go.

126
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,010
Thank you.

127
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:42,790
What brings you here today, Sakuraba?

128
00:11:44,690 --> 00:11:50,030
There's something I believe
you ought to know.

129
00:11:52,170 --> 00:11:54,910
I apologize if I'm meddling, but please.

130
00:11:55,680 --> 00:12:01,020
Take a look for yourself.

131
00:12:07,170 --> 00:12:10,010
I find issue with the second photograph.

132
00:12:12,890 --> 00:12:14,810
Is there something wrong here?

133
00:12:14,810 --> 00:12:16,940
Look carefully.

134
00:12:18,710 --> 00:12:21,180
Your wife's champagne.

135
00:12:22,100 --> 00:12:24,430
Does it not look odd to you?

136
00:12:27,860 --> 00:12:29,650
It's a darker blue.

137
00:12:30,530 --> 00:12:32,920
Isn't this a matter of lighting?

138
00:12:32,920 --> 00:12:35,410
Impossible.

139
00:12:35,410 --> 00:12:39,020
Her drink would not be this shade of blue,

140
00:12:39,020 --> 00:12:42,020
even if her glass were covered by a shadow.

141
00:12:43,740 --> 00:12:45,230
She was poisoned?

142
00:12:45,910 --> 00:12:47,720
I do not know.

143
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:54,000
But I couldn't bear to keep this to myself.

144
00:12:57,880 --> 00:12:59,450
Sakuraba!

145
00:13:00,460 --> 00:13:02,620
Sakuraba!

146
00:13:02,620 --> 00:13:06,000
Sakuraba! Sakuraba!

147
00:13:08,440 --> 00:13:10,670
I finally caught up.

148
00:13:10,670 --> 00:13:13,920
It's like I was screaming to a wall.

149
00:13:17,310 --> 00:13:21,690
Could I get that photograph you showed me?

150
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:26,800
I can't let this slide.

151
00:13:27,460 --> 00:13:30,400
Sayaka was poisoned.

152
00:13:32,140 --> 00:13:33,870
That's why...

153
00:13:36,020 --> 00:13:38,760
I plan to find the culprit myself.

154
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:44,110
Yourself? Why not report this to the police?

155
00:13:44,730 --> 00:13:49,430
I have my circumstances.

156
00:13:53,050 --> 00:13:56,080
Though I'm only a civil servant,

157
00:13:56,900 --> 00:13:59,660
I'll do what I can to uncover the truth.

158
00:14:00,780 --> 00:14:03,990
I can still file a report
after I've exhausted my own options.

159
00:14:09,640 --> 00:14:11,530
I understand.

160
00:14:11,530 --> 00:14:14,410
I'll send the pictures to you when I return.

161
00:14:14,410 --> 00:14:16,640
Though there are quite a few...

162
00:14:16,640 --> 00:14:18,460
Sakuraba.

163
00:14:20,710 --> 00:14:26,050
I vow to find this culprit.

164
00:14:27,470 --> 00:14:33,430
Still, I feel rather uncertain
working alone.

165
00:14:37,250 --> 00:14:39,030
If possible...

166
00:14:40,410 --> 00:14:43,450
Could you please assist me?

167
00:14:43,450 --> 00:14:46,020
Assist you...

168
00:14:46,760 --> 00:14:49,890
In finding the culprit?

169
00:14:50,970 --> 00:14:52,480
Yes.

170
00:14:54,640 --> 00:14:58,030
I think you should file a report after all.

171
00:14:58,030 --> 00:15:00,910
Besides, I'm only a photographer.

172
00:15:00,910 --> 00:15:02,540
But, Sakuraba...

173
00:15:05,410 --> 00:15:07,400
Sorry.

174
00:15:22,540 --> 00:15:24,830
[Town Hall]

175
00:15:25,840 --> 00:15:29,970
Sir, you forgot to specify
if this is your first marriage or not.

176
00:15:29,970 --> 00:15:33,110
You're right. I completely missed that.

177
00:15:33,110 --> 00:15:35,910
In that case, if you could please...

178
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:39,260
Here's a file for you.

179
00:15:39,260 --> 00:15:40,620
Thanks.

180
00:15:41,350 --> 00:15:44,100
We sure are busy today.

181
00:15:44,100 --> 00:15:46,590
Must be a lucky day.

182
00:15:46,590 --> 00:15:49,540
Did you submit your papers on a lucky day?

183
00:15:49,540 --> 00:15:51,170
Sure did.

184
00:15:52,080 --> 00:15:58,350
You filed your marriage at your own office.
How did that feel?

185
00:15:58,350 --> 00:16:00,710
Get back to work.

186
00:16:00,710 --> 00:16:04,530
Hey, no need to be so prickly.

187
00:16:04,530 --> 00:16:09,810
Or what, did something happen at the wedding?

188
00:16:11,400 --> 00:16:12,950
Kazuomi.

189
00:16:12,950 --> 00:16:14,990
Want to grab lunch?

190
00:16:16,400 --> 00:16:18,270
Sure.

191
00:16:19,290 --> 00:16:22,170
Quit cracking jokes, and start filing papers.

192
00:16:26,090 --> 00:16:27,990
Yes, sir.

193
00:16:30,580 --> 00:16:32,290
Thanks.

194
00:16:35,410 --> 00:16:36,930
What for?

195
00:17:00,200 --> 00:17:02,140
Kazu.

196
00:17:03,010 --> 00:17:05,070
Welcome home.

197
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:41,480
<i>Not the police.</i>

198
00:17:41,480 --> 00:17:45,920
<i>I think you should file a report after all.</i>

199
00:17:45,920 --> 00:17:49,090
<i>Besides, I'm only a photographer.</i>

200
00:18:19,940 --> 00:18:23,020
Sakuraba, are you home?

201
00:18:23,020 --> 00:18:24,700
This is Hayashida.

202
00:18:24,700 --> 00:18:26,470
Sakuraba.

203
00:18:28,000 --> 00:18:29,830
Sakuraba!

204
00:18:33,410 --> 00:18:35,190
- Sakuraba.
- Huh?

205
00:18:36,000 --> 00:18:37,650
Sachiko?

206
00:18:39,230 --> 00:18:41,420
Sakuraba.

207
00:18:52,320 --> 00:18:54,410
Please, lend me your strength.

208
00:18:56,950 --> 00:18:59,140
I need your help in finding the culprit.

209
00:18:59,140 --> 00:19:02,190
Why me?

210
00:19:03,110 --> 00:19:08,510
You know better than anyone
what occurred at that venue.

211
00:19:09,100 --> 00:19:11,120
But more importantly,

212
00:19:11,120 --> 00:19:15,190
you're the only other person who knows

213
00:19:16,570 --> 00:19:22,220
that Sayaka may have been poisoned.

214
00:19:22,220 --> 00:19:24,450
Still...

215
00:19:33,900 --> 00:19:35,610
Sayaka and I...

216
00:19:37,080 --> 00:19:40,230
We were to become husband and wife.

217
00:19:44,020 --> 00:19:47,940
I promised I would be by her side.

218
00:19:49,360 --> 00:19:52,030
I vowed to protect her.

219
00:19:54,450 --> 00:19:56,010
And yet...

220
00:19:58,460 --> 00:20:02,400
I can still see Sayaka collapsing.

221
00:20:03,210 --> 00:20:06,680
It's been seared to the back of my eyelids.

222
00:20:10,750 --> 00:20:12,210
So that's why...

223
00:20:14,550 --> 00:20:16,320
That's why...

224
00:20:19,340 --> 00:20:23,050
I can't let things end like this.

225
00:20:24,060 --> 00:20:29,650
I won't forgive whoever harmed my wife.

226
00:20:35,140 --> 00:20:38,980
You noticed the darker champagne.

227
00:20:39,550 --> 00:20:44,220
You noticed something I never would have.

228
00:20:45,750 --> 00:20:48,830
I can trust you, Sakuraba.

229
00:20:50,710 --> 00:20:53,740
My gut's telling me I can.

230
00:21:03,400 --> 00:21:05,530
Please.

231
00:21:07,250 --> 00:21:09,290
Please help me, for Sayaka's sake.

232
00:21:12,910 --> 00:21:14,430
Please.

233
00:21:16,090 --> 00:21:17,780
Please, I beg you.

234
00:21:19,150 --> 00:21:20,700
Please.

235
00:21:23,660 --> 00:21:25,650
Please, help me.

236
00:21:38,900 --> 00:21:41,130
Fine.

237
00:21:42,000 --> 00:21:43,200
What?

238
00:21:43,200 --> 00:21:47,140
I'm the one who informed you
of the potential poisoning.

239
00:21:47,140 --> 00:21:50,900
I feel a bit responsible
for seeing this through.

240
00:21:50,900 --> 00:21:52,400
Really?

241
00:21:53,290 --> 00:21:55,850
You'll help me?

242
00:21:56,340 --> 00:21:57,750
Sure.

243
00:22:00,020 --> 00:22:02,270
Thank you!

244
00:22:02,270 --> 00:22:04,420
I knew you were a good man.

245
00:22:04,420 --> 00:22:06,420
Personal space.

246
00:22:09,070 --> 00:22:10,690
Just one thing.

247
00:22:10,690 --> 00:22:12,920
Don't expect much from me, okay?

248
00:22:12,920 --> 00:22:15,980
It's not like I'm a detective or anything.

249
00:22:15,980 --> 00:22:19,290
I'm as much of an amateur as you are.

250
00:22:23,070 --> 00:22:27,290
<i>But there is one thing I can say for sure.</i>

251
00:22:27,290 --> 00:22:35,690
<i>All attendees of the wedding are suspects.</i>

252
00:22:36,350 --> 00:22:42,000
<i>And that includes the man
whose eyes I met first.</i>

253
00:22:42,850 --> 00:22:45,080
<i>That's right.</i>

254
00:22:46,090 --> 00:22:49,730
<i>He's just as much of a suspect, too.</i>

255
00:22:57,140 --> 00:23:01,210
Truth be told, I actually have one lead.

256
00:23:01,210 --> 00:23:02,760
A lead?

257
00:23:02,760 --> 00:23:04,920
The day before our ceremony...

258
00:23:06,860 --> 00:23:09,120
this letter was left in our mailbox.
